This paper deals with the problem of robot self-localization using machine learning techniques. The paper proposes a solution based on manifold learning and deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The problem of robot self-localization is a common problem in robotics (cs.RO) and the paper proposes a solution specifically for this problem. The paper also mentions the use of Kalman filtering, which is commonly used in control systems (cs.SY) and robotics research. Finally, the paper involves the use of geometrically motivated solutions, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research.
